Alex Hales is a 'special player', says James Taylor
Nottinghamshire batsman James Taylor believes team-mate Alex Hales is a "special" talent.Hales hit 99 for England in the Twenty20 international against the West Indiesat Trent Bridge on Sunday - the highest score by an Englishman in the shortest form of the game.Taylor toldBBC Radio Nottingham:"We all know what talent he has got."To represent your country you have to be a decent player, but Alex is a special player."